<p>Phoebe Booth Antiques LLC was founded by Phoebe Booth in 2011.  The Company specializes in the sale of fine antique English & Irish furniture and objet d'art, focusing on the Queen Anne and Georgian periods. Continental furniture is also represented and primarily focuses on authenticity, quality, condition and the lasting appeal of each piece. All decorative arts represented are meticulously selected and have great character which can only be achieved through age, patination and integrity.</p>

<p>In addition to selling exceptional European decorative arts from the 17th-19th centuries at antique shows around the country, Phoebe Booth Antiques LLC also sources inventory for clients - specific to individual style, dimensions and budget.</p>

<p>Phoebe Booth's personal expertise and invaluable contacts within the art world will provide a reliable foundation for collectors of all ages, designers, architects and dealers alike to source and purchase the most desirable antiques.</p>

<p>Ms. Booth is currently based in Chicago. Prior to founding Phoebe Booth Antiques LLC, she managed, for over four years, one of the world's leading decorative arts galleries based in New York. Phoebe Booth attended The Sotheby's American Arts program in 2005 and prior to pursuing her passion for decorative arts, worked on the Finance Team at The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation and in Equity Research at Morgan Stanley.</p>